{#
  qualification.jinja2 — Qualification-stage email template (2nd–4th exchange)
  Tenacious Consulting & Outsourcing SDR Agent

  Required variables:
    contact_first_name        (str)       — prospect's first name
    company_name              (str)       — prospect company name
    their_last_message        (str)       — verbatim or paraphrased summary of what
                                           the prospect said in their last reply
    next_qualification_question (str)     — the next unanswered qualification question
                                           (one of Q1–Q4 from the system prompt)
    answered_questions        (list[str]) — list of questions already answered, used
                                           to avoid repetition and to show progress
    is_qualified              (bool)      — True when all 4 questions are answered;
                                           triggers calendar booking CTA
    calendar_link             (str|None)  — Cal.com booking URL, required if is_qualified

  Qualification questions (for reference — pass the text as next_qualification_question):
    Q1: What specific engineering initiative or project is the top priority right now?
    Q2: What is the timeline or milestone pressure on that initiative?
    Q3: What is currently blocking or slowing that initiative?
    Q4: Who else is involved in the decision to bring in external engineering support?

  Guardrail notes:
    - This template is only used after the prospect has replied at least once.
    - tone_checker.enforce() must be called on the rendered output before send.
    - One ask per message — next_qualification_question must be a single question.
    - If is_qualified is True, calendar_link must not be None.
#}

{{ contact_first_name }},

{% if their_last_message %}
Thanks for that — helpful context.
{% if answered_questions %}

To summarize what I've got so far:
{% for q in answered_questions %}
- {{ q }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if not is_qualified %}
One more thing to make sure we'd actually be useful to you before suggesting next steps:

{{ next_qualification_question }}

Happy to answer any questions about how we typically work in the meantime.

{% else %}
Based on what you've shared, this sounds like a good match for how we engage — a scoped
squad, bounded timeline, specific outcome.

The right next step is a 25-minute call with one of our technical leads at Tenacious.
They can walk through stack fit, team composition, and what a first sprint would look like.

You can grab time here: {{ calendar_link }}

No prep needed on your end.

{% endif %}

{% if not is_qualified %}
No pressure — if the timing is off or the fit isn't there, good to know that too.
{% endif %}
